{"ID":270208, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"208\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs207.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs209.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 208<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Spirits Eternal<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Without attempting to describe this mysterious connection, and the laws that govern the body\n  and the spirit of man,<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> their relationship to each other, and the design of God<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> in relation to the\n  human body and spirit, I would just remark, that the spirits of men are eternal,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> that they are\n  governed by the same Priesthood that Abraham, Melchizedek, and the Apostles were: that they are\n  organized<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> according to that Priesthood which is everlasting,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> &ldquo;without beginning of days or end of\n  years,&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span>&mdash;that they all move in their respective spheres, and are governed by the law of God;<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> that\n  when they appear upon the earth they are in a probationary state,<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> and are preparing, if righteous,\n  for a future and greater glory; that the spirits of good men cannot interfere with the wicked beyond\n  their prescribed bounds, for Michael, the Archangel, dared not bring a railing accusation against the\n  devil, but said, &ldquo;The Lord rebuke thee, Satan.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Wicked Spirits Restricted in Power<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">It would seem also, that wicked spirits have their bounds, limits, and laws by which they are\n  governed or controlled, and know their future destiny; hence, those that were in the maniac said to\n  our Savior, &ldquo;Art thou come to torment us before the time,&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> and when Satan presented himself\n  before the Lord, among the sons of God, he said that he came &ldquo;from going to and fro in the earth,\n  and from wandering up and down in it;&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> and he is emphatically called the prince of the power of\n  the air;<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> and, it is very evident that they possess a power that none but those who have the\n  Priesthood can control, as we have before adverted to, in the case of the sons of Sceva.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Having said so much upon the general principles, without referring to the peculiar situation,\n  power, and influence of the magicians of Egypt,<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> the wizards<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> and witches<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> of the Jews, the oracles\n  of the heathen, their necromancers,<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> soothsayers,<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> and astrologers,<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> the maniacs or those possessed\n  of devils in the Apostles&rsquo; days,<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> we will notice, and try to detect (so far as we have the Scriptures\n  for our aid) some few instances of the development of false spirits in more modern times, and in this\n  our day.<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">False Prophets<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">The &ldquo;French Prophets&rdquo; were possessed of a spirit that deceived; they existed in Vivaris and\n  Dauphany, in great num-<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114808\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114808)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114808)\">D&amp;C 88:15<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117074\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117074)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117074)\">Abr. 5:8<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113094\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113094)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113094)\">D&amp;C 3:1<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114060\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114060)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114060)\">D&amp;C 58:3<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115041\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115041)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115041)\">D&amp;C 93:33<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117040\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117040)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117040)\">Abr. 3:22<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106219\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106219)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106219)\">Ex. 40:15<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106265\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106265)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106265)\">Num. 25:13<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116281\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116281)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116281)\">D&amp;C 131:2<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111931\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111931)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111931)\">Alma 13:7<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114621\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114621)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114621)\">D&amp;C 84:17<\/a><\/span>\n  